{
  "stem": "12462.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So Colonel Brennan called up Goldberg and persuaded him to let me go on a temporary basis.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it-- it turned out to be-- it turned out to be quite a few months.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It turned out to be almost a year.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I was still in the Labor Branch, traveling out in Wisconsin and Michigan and Illinois at the time of V-E Day.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And just before that, I had read Justice Jackson's first report to President Truman.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In the newspapers.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then I-- using connections-- got a full copy.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I was so impressed by that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I had the impression that if I got with Justice Jackson [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and his staff, I would be able to make a contribution.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I immediately arranged to fly back to Washington.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And with a fraternity brother who was one of the assistants to General 'Wild Bill' Donovan, I got in to see the-- another Donovan, Commander Donovan, who was the head-- the-- the legal advisor of OSS.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And within a half hour, he hired me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He then telephoned out to-- had someone telephone out to Chicago and say that I was not going to return because the OSS had conscripted me.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Whereupon I started to study OSS documents and get ready to go to present materials to the prosecution staff.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And in various ways I did that and later got on the prosecution staff myself.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "General Donovan was the head of the Office of Strategic Services.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I'd met him in Africa when I was with the Office of Strategic Services there, but it was a very casual meeting.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was merely a lieutenant training people, and he had a lot of other more important officers than me to deal with.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
